\begin_layout Standard
The online data archive contains the following data sets in Stata format:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
workfile2012.dta
\emph default
 provides data for 722 Commuting Zones times 5 time periods (1950-1970,
 1970-1980, 1980-1990, 1990-2000, 2000-2005).
 All variables with the prefix 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\emph on
l_
\emph default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 refer to start-of-period values while variables with the prefix 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\emph on
d_
\emph default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 correspond to 10-year equivalent changes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
occ1990dd_data2012.dta
\emph default
 provides data for the 330 occupations of the 
\emph on
occ1990dd
\emph default
 occupation panel.
 Variables are defined for the years 1950, 1970, 1980, 1990, 2000, and 2005.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
emp-bypctile-1980-2005-rewt-0-*.dta
\emph default
, 
\emph on
emp-bypctile-1980-2005-rewt-1980-*.dta
\emph default
, 
\emph on
dwg-byperc-1980-2005-*.dta
\emph default
, and 
\emph on
occ-means-by-decade-1980-2005-*.dta 
\emph default
provide occupation-level data for polarization graphs, drawing either on
 the full set of commuting zones (suffix 
\emph on
czall
\emph default
) or only on commuting zones with high or low routine employment share (suffix
 
\emph on
czhigh-abovemean-RSHA
\emph default
 or 
\emph on
czlow-abovemean-RSHA
\emph default
).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
plotpoints-svc-by-quintile-1970-2005.dta
\emph default
 and 
\emph on
RTI-bypctile.dta
\emph default
 provide data for employment shares in the bottom quintile of the occupational
 skill distribution, and for routine intensity by skill percentile.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These data files are the basis for all reported empirical results except
 Panel B of Table 7 which draws on individual-level Census microdata.
\end_layout

